<subSubSection pageId="28" pageNumber="29" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="28.[151,1437,510,1942]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,510,536]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[280,499,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendidus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[280,499,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Colletes splendidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[506,595,511,537]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[506,595,511,537]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
unequivocally belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morawitz" authorityYear="1876" box="[932,1068,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypearis">
<emphasis box="[932,1068,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. clypearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, the constituent species of which are characterized by malar area relatively long, at least half as long as basal width of mandible (
<figureCitation box="[1317,1422,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1189,1213]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1164]" captionTargetId="figure-19@30.[151,1435,181,1165]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 17. Diagnostic features of the male of C. splendidus sp. nov. (A) Head in profile showing relative size of malar area; (B) oblique view of metasoma showing the long erect hairs of T1; posterodorsal view of metasoma showing (C) the presence of well-defined apical bands and (D) truncate apical margin of T7. Scale bars: (A–C) 1 mm; (D) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226695/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 17A</figureCitation>
); T1 disc without tomentum and sparsely covered with long erect hairs (
<figureCitation box="[932,1033,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1189,1213]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1164]" captionTargetId="figure-19@30.[151,1435,181,1165]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 17. Diagnostic features of the male of C. splendidus sp. nov. (A) Head in profile showing relative size of malar area; (B) oblique view of metasoma showing the long erect hairs of T1; posterodorsal view of metasoma showing (C) the presence of well-defined apical bands and (D) truncate apical margin of T7. Scale bars: (A–C) 1 mm; (D) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226695/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 17B</figureCitation>
); tergal apical bands well developed (
<figureCitation box="[160,265,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1189,1213]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1164]" captionTargetId="figure-19@30.[151,1435,181,1165]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 17. Diagnostic features of the male of C. splendidus sp. nov. (A) Head in profile showing relative size of malar area; (B) oblique view of metasoma showing the long erect hairs of T1; posterodorsal view of metasoma showing (C) the presence of well-defined apical bands and (D) truncate apical margin of T7. Scale bars: (A–C) 1 mm; (D) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226695/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 17C</figureCitation>
); male T7 relatively broad with a truncate apex (
<figureCitation box="[842,949,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="30.[151,250,1189,1213]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1164]" captionTargetId="figure-19@30.[151,1435,181,1165]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 17. Diagnostic features of the male of C. splendidus sp. nov. (A) Head in profile showing relative size of malar area; (B) oblique view of metasoma showing the long erect hairs of T1; posterodorsal view of metasoma showing (C) the presence of well-defined apical bands and (D) truncate apical margin of T7. Scale bars: (A–C) 1 mm; (D) 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5226695" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5226695/files/figure.png" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Fig. 17D</figureCitation>
); and male S7 broad basally and strongly narrowing towards apex (Fig. 16F) (
<bibRefCitation author="Noskiewicz, J." box="[566,767,655,681]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 531" refId="ref43629" refString="Noskiewicz, J. (1936) Die palaarktischen Colletes - Arten. Prace Naukowe Wydawnictwo Towarzystwa Naukowego we Lwowie, 3, 1 - 531." type="journal article" year="1936">Noskiewicz 1936</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Niu, Z. Q. &amp; Zhu, C. D. &amp; Kuhlmann, M." box="[781,980,655,682]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" pagination="101 - 151" refId="ref43432" refString="Niu, Z. Q., Zhu, C. D. &amp; Kuhlmann, M. (2013 b) Bees of the Colletes clypearis - group (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Colletidae) from China with description of seven new species. Zootaxa, 3745 (2), 101 - 151. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3745.2.1" type="journal article" year="2013">
Niu 
<emphasis box="[832,883,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">et al</emphasis>
., 2013b
</bibRefCitation>
). Among the species of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Morawitz" authorityYear="1876" box="[1299,1437,655,681]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="clypearis">
<emphasis box="[1299,1437,655,681]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. clypearis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group found in 
<collectingRegion box="[322,406,691,717]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">Xizang</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[415,567,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendidus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[415,567,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. splendidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[573,661,691,717]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[573,661,691,717]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is most similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2002" box="[864,990,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibeticus">
<emphasis box="[864,990,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. tibeticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2002" box="[1043,1222,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paratibeticus">
<emphasis box="[1043,1222,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. paratibeticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, however, it can be differentiated from both by the mesosoma covered mostly with bright brownish pubescence (mesosomal pubescence with mostly off-white to pale-yellow hairs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2002" box="[653,780,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibeticus">
<emphasis box="[653,780,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. tibeticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2002" box="[832,1012,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paratibeticus">
<emphasis box="[832,1012,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. paratibeticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Both sexes of 
<taxonomicName box="[1190,1342,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendidus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1190,1342,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. splendidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1348,1436,763,789]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1348,1436,763,789]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
can be further distinguished from those of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2002" box="[621,801,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paratibeticus">
<emphasis box="[621,801,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. paratibeticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the paraocular area having only pale hairs (paraocular area with a distinct longitudinal band of black hairs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2002" box="[774,956,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paratibeticus">
<emphasis box="[774,956,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. paratibeticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Males of 
<taxonomicName box="[1088,1242,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="splendidus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1088,1242,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. splendidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1250,1341,835,861]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1250,1341,835,861]" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
are also different from that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2002" box="[398,527,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibeticus">
<emphasis box="[398,527,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. tibeticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having a comparatively broad hind basitarsus, which is 3.8× as long as broad (hind basitarsus 4.6× as long as broad in males of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2002" box="[713,840,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibeticus">
<emphasis box="[713,840,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. tibeticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); females are different by the presence of black hairs on mesoscutum and scutellum (mesoscutum and scutellum without black hairs in females of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kuhlmann" authorityYear="2002" box="[1191,1319,943,969]" class="Insecta" family="Colletidae" genus="Colletes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="28" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tibeticus">
<emphasis box="[1191,1319,943,969]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="29">C. tibeticus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
